The City Budget Officer commented that the project was intended for the development of the City.
The COA Audit Team explained that if the project was computed on a per-item basis over the total cost, it would be classified under the semi-expendable property only. He also suggested that the project could be incorporated into the road network instead of being treated as a standalone project, allowing it to be charged against other funds, as the 20% Development Fund (DF) has outlined specific guidelines for such allocations.
The City Engineer reported that six projects were completed in 2024, seven in 2023, and three in prior years.  He also added that most projects in CY 2020, 2021, and 2022 were almost completed and will be completed within the year.
The City Budget Officer further explained that the general guidelines for the utilization of the 20% DF state that the projects are essential to the promotion of the general welfare of the people.
The COA Audit Team emphasized that although the project would be beneficial to the public, it would also be in a nature of investment or capital expenditures and provide direct developmental benefits to be eligible under the 20% DF.

