The Municipal Accountant review the long outstanding stale checks and take up the necessary entry reversing to Cash-in Bank and Accounts Payable or Unappropriated Surplus, whichever is applicable, the amounts thereof;
The Municipal Treasurer to cancel the unclaimed stale checks and furnish the accountant with the original disbursement vouchers (DV) and its supporting documents, for the preparation of the Journal Voucher/s.

We reiterated our prior years’ audit recommendation that the Local Chief Executive:
require the Inventory Committee to complete the “One-Time Cleansing of PPE accounts” as provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006, so that only serviceable and existing items at year-end are reported as PPE to allow fair presentation of the PPE accounts in the year-end financial statements;
direct the GSO and the Accounting Office to conduct reconciliation of RPCPPE and PPE account balances;
oblige the GSO to assign more specific classification of the PPE using the Revised Chart of accounts, to tally with Accounting Office;
order the Inventory team to identify if the variances are non-existing/missing or unrecorded PPE as well as the persons accountable for proper disposition based on Sections 7 to 9 of COA Circular 2020-006;
direct the GSO to reclassify the previously classified semi-expendable items costing ₱50,000.00 or more to the appropriate PPE account, prepare PAR for all PPE acquired, and include it in the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment;
direct the Appraisal Committee to give the appraisal cost of the semi-expendable PE without value; and
designate a personnel/team which shall be responsible for securing the land titles of the 162 lots and likewise appropriate funds to cover its cost.

We recommended and Management agreed to :
immediately require the contractor to post warranty security to cover the structural defects/failures;
issue the Certificate of Final Acceptance after the defects liability period which is one year after the project completion;
require contractors to post performance security from the signing of the contract up to the issuance of Certificate of Final Acceptance; and
henceforth, strictly enforce the posting of the performance security and warranty security as specified in Section 39 and Section 62.2.3 of the IRR of RA 9184.

We recommended Management to require the Municipal Accountant to:
