check the transactions and schedule of the Tabaco Community College Accounts Payable and make the necessary reconciliation to remove the negative balance in the SL;
review the accounting errors noted and record the necessary adjusting entries to correct the Accounts Payable balances;
obtain the pertinent report from the Municipal Engineering Office to verify the actual physical accomplishments of infrastructure projects as basis for accrual at year-end;
strictly comply with the accrual basis of accounting in preparing the financial statements in accordance with the IPSAS; and
improve the accounting controls over the monitoring of payables and maintenance of necessary records.

We recommended and Management agreed to :
