require the Municipal Engineering Office to expedite the preparation of the necessary detailed engineering activities to avoid delays in the procurement for the infrastructure projects;
consider third party contractors to implement projects in lieu of projects thru administration to decrease delays;
through the Local Development Council, evaluate and plan thoroughly the proposed priority development projects to be included in the Annual Investment Plan and ensure that these are procurement-and-implementation ready;
enforce the monitoring and evaluation of the implementation of development programs, projects and activities by the Local Development Council in accordance with the approved development plan; and
plan the intended use of savings from the completed projects.

We recommended that Management:
direct the Accounting Office and the MDRRM Office to regularly prepare a Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF;
oblige the Accounting Office to maintain Subsidiary Ledgers, showing detailed appropriations and utilizations, specific fund source, transferring agency, donor, and year transferred;
direct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to coordinate with the LDRRM Officer to determine the actual balance to be transferred to the Special Trust Fund based on the Report on the Sources and Utilization and subsidiary ledgers; and
require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to effect the transfer of the cash equivalent of the unexpended LDRRMF balance for CY 2023 and prior years, to the LDRRM Special Trust in compliance with COA Circular No. 2012-002.

We reiterated our recommendation that Management:
determine the root cause why these PPAs are not timely implemented;
establish specific measures to increase the implementation of the SEF programs, projects and activities;
exert effort to ensure that the Special Education Fund of the Municipality is efficiently utilized and that the implementation of all identified PPAs be given priority to warrant the full attainment of goals in accordance with DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Circular (JC) No. 1, series of 2017; and
monitor regularly the progress of each PPA’s implementation to achieve the desired level of efficiency.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
