The Municipal Engineer coordinate with the contractor with regard the required supporting documents in order to immediately process payment for the work accomplished and to enable the Municipal Accountant to timely record progress payments and record the appropriate CIP accounts in the LGU books;

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Accountant to trace the transactions recorded in the Due from Other Funds and Due to Other Funds accounts and take up the necessary adjustments in the books to arrive at an accurate balance of the financial statements in keeping with Section 111 of P.D. 1445;
The Municipal Treasurer, after the Municipal Accountant has prepared all the necessary adjustments, to cause the payment of any payables to the concerned fund in order to eliminate the reciprocal accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that Management require:
